 salon charges $24.99 for a haircut. I mean, it's my hair and they are cutting it off of my head and not even giving me anything back for it! How could that be worth $24.99?<br>
<br>
Then I went out to lunch. Damn restaurant wanted $6.50 for a hamburger. I mean a hamburger. A dead cow, some baked flour and grains decorated with plants that grow from the ground. I mean who the hell wants to buy a dead cow??<br>
<br>
Everquest reflects a lot of aspects of modern society. In real life, you pay for goods and services such as hamburgers and haircuts- just like you pay a baker to make those Halas 10lb Pies or for a necro to locate your corpse... or an enchanter to cast KEI.<br>
<br>
You don't need KEI. Really... you don't. Can you believe a time existed when there was no KEI? People actually managed to level without that 14 mana a tic magical goodness!<br>
<br>
But as in life, not everyone is a greedy Ebaneezer Scrooge looking to milk every last penny from you. You make friends. You form alliances. You do good onto others and you'll have good done unto you. You give away KEi and that druid promises free ports forever. YAY! You made a friend!<br>
<br>
Quite frankly, since I was indebted to a friend for helping me buy my scroll of KEI, I did actively KEI for donations to gather cash to pay him back. I don't do it now because I am in a very active guild and really don't have the time to sit for an 8 hour KEI casting shift (people actually sit there that long... I would have hung myself with my mouse cord) but I'll cast it if someone asks... properly while I'm passing through. No, they don't have to offer me riches, though I'm not above accepting donations graciously (and more often that not, one donation=lifetime of KEI from me unless I really don't like you), but you have to treat me with respect be polite with me. &quot;Gimme KEI&quot; will get you ignored. Asking me to leave a camp/group I'm at just to KEI you is incredibly rude. Getting impatient with me when you ambush my camp requesting KEI and I can't cast it as soon as you think you need it will get you laughed at. Be respectful of my time in game. As a high end player, there are things I am responsible for doing.. like showing up for a raid on time that may make it less likely I' can stop and KEI 10 people in the Nexus... but if I'm standing around emoting at people, I don't care if you don't even have 1cp, just be polite. <br>
<br>
900 mana on a 4000 mana pool= 4.444444 casts of KEI. Then the average chanter's mana pool is wiped out. That's not very many casts. One trip through the Nexus and I can be oom 3 times over with requests when the normal KEI corner vendors have shop closed up. Really, if you were a 60+ enc who doesn't go on role/anon everywhere (and I don't because it's easier for guild to keep track of who's who and who's where and I'm also quite proud I'm 65 and I don't like to hide it... besides everyone knows I'm an enc anyway, except the guy who always asks me for a TL, but that's another story. <p>-Mistress Enraptura Failsafe-<br>
Phantasmist<br>
