<br>
I think my issue with the complaining is that generally I sell to three classes of people:<br>
<br>
1 - Greens<br>
2 - Soloers off to Quad<br>
3 - Druids about to sell ports<br>
<br>
If you are in my guild, KEI is free.  If you are in my group, KEI is free.  If you are my friend, KEI is free.  If I am in a good mood, KEI is free.<br>
<br>
I have a cleric alt who has never charged for a rezz.  I do want to remind people of the olden days, when it was heck to find a 39+ cleric for an xp rezz and a 49+ cleric for a 90% rezz.  With lots of people well above those marks and lower level clerics with rezz, the power to charge for rezzes went down.<br>
<br>
Same thing with Ports.  Used to be Druids and Wizards made lots of money porting people.  Anybody with Pop needs a Druid/Wizard to get to 1 place.....Western Wastes.  They are handy to get to Katta Castelum and NK but PoP has cut the old revene stream.<br>
<br>
So, where does that leave folk?  Well, I now see people selling PoTC and Virtue.  Guess clerics and druids found another revenue stream.  Note, ever notice the number of druids in RM....I wonder why?<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Spiritual Son of Harry<br>
